The fix is clean. Here's a summary:

**Problem**: The `state failures tools` subcommand (in `handle_tool_failures` at line 856) called `build_tool_failures_report()`, but that function was never written — only the dispatch plumbing was added.

**Fix**: Added the missing `build_tool_failures_report` function (lines 1936–2007) right after `build_recent_failure_report`. It:

• Filters events for `ToolCallCompleted` type
• Detects failures via three payload signals: `error` field present, `status: "failed"/"error"`, or `success: false`
• Formats each row with timestamp (ISO), tool name (bold), error summary (red, truncated to 80 chars at char boundary), and run_id (dimmed)
• Returns `"no tool failures found"` when no matching events exist
• Default limit of 10 from the caller, overridable via `--limit N`

